{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SLcWmAqPub864d4XkB9Gdi","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete content of the game-settled.ts handler file:\n\n## Handler Structure Overview\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/game-settled.ts`\n\nThe handler is a queue event processor that orchestrates the challenge engine when games settle. Here's the key structure:\n\n### Main Processing Flow\n\n1. **Validation** (lines 145-157): Extracts and validates payload (roundId, game, players, feeLamports, settledAt)\n\n2. **Reward Pool Funding** (lines 159-164): Emits a `REWARD_POOL_FUND` event once per round\n\n3. **Per-Player Processing Loop** (lines 167-292):\n   - Quest eligibility check (skip refunded games)\n   - Challenge progress evaluation via adapters\n   - Reward emission on completion\n   - Wager-based points grant\n   - Crate drop roll\n\n### Assignment Completion Mechanism\n\nThe handler marks assignments as completed in the `markAssignmentCompleted` function (lines 122-131):\n\n```typescript\nexport async function markAssignmentCompleted(\n  db: Db,\n  assignmentId: string,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE challenge_assignments\n    SET status = 'completed', completed_at = now()\n    WHERE id = ${assignmentId}\n  `;\n}\n```\n\nThis is called at **line 228** when `newProgress >= assignment.target`, indicating the challenge is complete. The update atomically sets `status = 'completed'` and records the timestamp.\n\n### Completion Workflow\n\nWhen a challenge reaches its target (lines 226-263):\n\n1. Assignment is marked as completed (line 228)\n2. Reward intent is emitted based on `reward_type`:\n   - **points**: Emits `POINTS_GRANT` event (lines 231-238)\n   - **crate**: Emits `CRATE_DROP` event (lines 239-246)\n3. Completion bonus is checked (lines 256-262) via `checkCompletionBonus()`\n\n### Hooking in Onboarding Chain Progression\n\n**Entry Point for Hook**: Around **lines 226-263** (the completion detection block)\n\nYou can hook onboarding chain progression here:\n- **After line 228** (`markAssignmentCompleted`): Insert logic to check if this challenge is part of an onboarding sequence and advance the user's onboarding state\n- **Before line 231**: Fetch the user's onboarding context to determine if reward should trigger progression\n- **After line 256** (after `checkCompletionBonus`): Emit an onboarding progression event if needed\n\nThe transaction wrapper (`db.withTransaction`) ensures your hook runs atomically with progress updates, and the structure allows you to emit additional events or update onboarding tables within the same transaction."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8262916-ffcb-4b28-90e1-2b18f6c84ba5","uuid":"a697cbe0-97fb-4a24-b24a-510f131d139f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:34:02.075Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/game-settled.ts` completely and report its full content. I need to understand the handler structure, how it marks assignments completed, and where I can hook in onboarding chain progression.","agentId":"a2309fb2af002c509","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete content of the game-settled.ts handler file:\n\n## Handler Structure Overview\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/game-settled.ts`\n\nThe handler is a queue event processor that orchestrates the challenge engine when games settle. Here's the key structure:\n\n### Main Processing Flow\n\n1. **Validation** (lines 145-157): Extracts and validates payload (roundId, game, players, feeLamports, settledAt)\n\n2. **Reward Pool Funding** (lines 159-164): Emits a `REWARD_POOL_FUND` event once per round\n\n3. **Per-Player Processing Loop** (lines 167-292):\n   - Quest eligibility check (skip refunded games)\n   - Challenge progress evaluation via adapters\n   - Reward emission on completion\n   - Wager-based points grant\n   - Crate drop roll\n\n### Assignment Completion Mechanism\n\nThe handler marks assignments as completed in the `markAssignmentCompleted` function (lines 122-131):\n\n```typescript\nexport async function markAssignmentCompleted(\n  db: Db,\n  assignmentId: string,\n): Promise<void> {\n  await db.rawSql`\n    UPDATE challenge_assignments\n    SET status = 'completed', completed_at = now()\n    WHERE id = ${assignmentId}\n  `;\n}\n```\n\nThis is called at **line 228** when `newProgress >= assignment.target`, indicating the challenge is complete. The update atomically sets `status = 'completed'` and records the timestamp.\n\n### Completion Workflow\n\nWhen a challenge reaches its target (lines 226-263):\n\n1. Assignment is marked as completed (line 228)\n2. Reward intent is emitted based on `reward_type`:\n   - **points**: Emits `POINTS_GRANT` event (lines 231-238)\n   - **crate**: Emits `CRATE_DROP` event (lines 239-246)\n3. Completion bonus is checked (lines 256-262) via `checkCompletionBonus()`\n\n### Hooking in Onboarding Chain Progression\n\n**Entry Point for Hook**: Around **lines 226-263** (the completion detection block)\n\nYou can hook onboarding chain progression here:\n- **After line 228** (`markAssignmentCompleted`): Insert logic to check if this challenge is part of an onboarding sequence and advance the user's onboarding state\n- **Before line 231**: Fetch the user's onboarding context to determine if reward should trigger progression\n- **After line 256** (after `checkCompletionBonus`): Emit an onboarding progression event if needed\n\nThe transaction wrapper (`db.withTransaction`) ensures your hook runs atomically with progress updates, and the structure allows you to emit additional events or update onboarding tables within the same transaction."}],"totalDurationMs":11216,"totalTokens":34326,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8063,"cache_read_input_tokens":25575,"output_tokens":683,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8063},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
