{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012t83rEKUYNg6927DoaKqhs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete content of the completion-bonus.ts file:\n\nThe file contains three DB helper functions that follow a clear pattern:\n\n1. **getCompletionBonuses** (lines 28-38): Fetches active completion bonuses for a campaign using a typed query (`db.rawSql<CompletionBonus[]>`)\n\n2. **countCompletedAssignments** (lines 43-58): Counts completed challenge assignments for a user in a period, using a COUNT(*) aggregation and parsing the text count back to a number\n\n3. **insertBonusCompletion** (lines 64-77): Inserts a bonus completion record with an idempotency guard via `ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING`, returning a boolean indicating whether the insert actually succeeded\n\n**Main handler**: `checkCompletionBonus` (lines 91-147) is the exported function called from the game-settled handler. It:\n- Fetches all active bonuses for a campaign\n- For each bonus, counts completed assignments for the user in the period\n- If the count meets the required threshold and the bonus hasn't been awarded yet (idempotency check), it:\n  - Inserts the bonus completion record\n  - Emits either a POINTS_GRANT or CRATE_DROP event based on reward_type\n  - Logs the award\n\nThe pattern shows DB helpers are called sequentially within the main async function, with the database transaction handling delegated to the caller (the game-settled handler). All DB operations use `db.rawSql` with template literals and parameterized queries for SQL injection safety."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8262916-ffcb-4b28-90e1-2b18f6c84ba5","uuid":"58be4a4d-cecd-499c-8148-89755ed4b2f8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:34:02.526Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/completion-bonus.ts` completely and report its full content. I need to see the pattern for DB helpers and how it's called from game-settled handler.","agentId":"ae442214a3fddee68","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete content of the completion-bonus.ts file:\n\nThe file contains three DB helper functions that follow a clear pattern:\n\n1. **getCompletionBonuses** (lines 28-38): Fetches active completion bonuses for a campaign using a typed query (`db.rawSql<CompletionBonus[]>`)\n\n2. **countCompletedAssignments** (lines 43-58): Counts completed challenge assignments for a user in a period, using a COUNT(*) aggregation and parsing the text count back to a number\n\n3. **insertBonusCompletion** (lines 64-77): Inserts a bonus completion record with an idempotency guard via `ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING`, returning a boolean indicating whether the insert actually succeeded\n\n**Main handler**: `checkCompletionBonus` (lines 91-147) is the exported function called from the game-settled handler. It:\n- Fetches all active bonuses for a campaign\n- For each bonus, counts completed assignments for the user in the period\n- If the count meets the required threshold and the bonus hasn't been awarded yet (idempotency check), it:\n  - Inserts the bonus completion record\n  - Emits either a POINTS_GRANT or CRATE_DROP event based on reward_type\n  - Logs the award\n\nThe pattern shows DB helpers are called sequentially within the main async function, with the database transaction handling delegated to the caller (the game-settled handler). All DB operations use `db.rawSql` with template literals and parameterized queries for SQL injection safety."}],"totalDurationMs":7199,"totalTokens":32432,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5776,"cache_read_input_tokens":26287,"output_tokens":364,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5776},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],