{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011TgKHX9MnRxSyLdxvnPaLH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Integration Test Patterns Report\n\nBased on the integration test file at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`, here are the key test patterns:\n\n### 1. Challenge Setup & Assignment Creation\n\nTests look up challenges from the database and create assignments:\n\n```typescript\n// Look up the 'Play 3 Games' daily challenge\nconst challenges = await rawSql<{ id: string }[]>`\n  SELECT id FROM challenges WHERE title = 'Play 3 Games' LIMIT 1\n`;\nexpect(challenges.length).toBe(1);\nconst challengeId = challenges[0]!.id;\n\n// Create an active assignment for this user\nawait rawSql`\n  INSERT INTO challenge_assignments (user_id, challenge_id, period_key, target)\n  VALUES (${userId}, ${challengeId}, 'daily:2026-04-03', 3)\n`;\n```\n\nFor completion bonus tests, fetch challenges with attributes:\n\n```typescript\nconst dailyChallenges = await rawSql<{ id: string; action: string; scope: string }[]>`\n  SELECT id, action, scope FROM challenges\n  WHERE campaign_id = ${campaignId} AND is_active = true\n  ORDER BY sort_order ASC\n  LIMIT 3\n`;\n\n// Create 3 assignments with mixed statuses\nawait rawSql`\n  INSERT INTO challenge_assignments (user_id, challenge_id, period_key, target, progress, status, completed_at)\n  VALUES\n    (${userId}, ${dailyChallenges[0]!.id}, ${periodKey}, 1, 1, 'completed', now()),\n    (${userId}, ${dailyChallenges[1]!.id}, ${periodKey}, 1, 1, 'completed', now()),\n    (${userId}, ${dailyChallenges[2]!.id}, ${periodKey}, 1, 0, 'active', NULL)\n`;\n```\n\n### 2. Verifying Assignment Status Changes\n\nTests verify progress and status updates after events:\n\n```typescript\n// Verify progress incremented to 1 with active status\nconst assignments = await rawSql<{ progress: number; status: string }[]>`\n  SELECT progress, status FROM challenge_assignments WHERE user_id = ${userId}\n`;\nexpect(assignments[0]!.progress).toBe(1);\nexpect(assignments[0]!.status).toBe(\"active\");\n\n// Verify completion (with completed_at timestamp)\nconst assignments = await rawSql<{ progress: number; status: string; completed_at: string | null }[]>`\n  SELECT progress, status, completed_at FROM challenge_assignments WHERE user_id = ${userId}\n`;\nexpect(assignments[0]!.progress).toBe(1);\nexpect(assignments[0]!.status).toBe(\"completed\");\nexpect(assignments[0]!.completed_at).not.toBeNull();\n\n// Verify bonus completion tracking\nconst bonuses = await rawSql<{ user_id: string; bonus_id: string; period_key: string }[]>`\n  SELECT user_id, bonus_id, period_key FROM bonus_completions\n  WHERE user_id = ${userId}\n`;\nexpect(bonuses.length).toBe(1);\nexpect(bonuses[0]!.period_key).toBe(periodKey);\n```\n\n### 3. TRUNCATE Pattern in beforeEach\n\nThe test suite truncates 21 tables in a single TRUNCATE statement with RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE:\n\n```typescript\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  // Clean tables for isolation\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, closecall_rounds, closecall_candles, operator_events, event_queue, game_entries, transactions, player_profiles, referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates, reward_pool_fundings, point_grants, player_points, dogpile_events, crate_drops, progress_events, challenge_assignments, bonus_completions RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n  \n  // Reset reward_pool balance to zero (keep singleton row from migration seed)\n  await rawSql`UPDATE reward_pool SET balance_lamports = 0, lifetime_funded = 0, lifetime_paid = 0, updated_at = now() WHERE id = 1`;\n  \n  // Reset PlatformConfig cache so each test reads from its own mock\n  resetPlatformConfigCache();\n});\n```\n\n### 4. DB Setup (createDb, Migrations, etc.)\n\nIn `beforeAll`:\n\n```typescript\nbeforeAll(async () => {\n  rawSql = makeSql();  // Creates postgres connection\n  \n  // Drop and recreate tables in test (referral-related)\n  await rawSql`DROP TABLE IF EXISTS referral_claims, referral_earnings, referral_links, referral_codes, referral_kol_rates CASCADE`;\n  \n  // Create custom tables for testing...\n  await rawSql`CREATE TABLE referral_codes ( ... )`;\n  // ... more CREATE TABLE statements ...\n  \n  // Initialize db wrapper\n  db = createDb(DATABASE_URL, rawSql);\n});\n\nafterAll(async () => {\n  await db.close();\n  await rawSql.end();\n});\n```\n\nDatabase URL defaults to:\n```typescript\nconst DATABASE_URL = process.env.DATABASE_URL ?? \"postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev\";\n```\n\n### 5. Full Table List in TRUNCATE Statement\n\n**21 tables** truncated in beforeEach:\n\n1. `rounds`\n2. `closecall_rounds`\n3. `closecall_candles`\n4. `operator_events`\n5. `event_queue`\n6. `game_entries`\n7. `transactions`\n8. `player_profiles`\n9. `referral_codes`\n10. `referral_links`\n11. `referral_earnings`\n12. `referral_claims`\n13. `referral_kol_rates`\n14. `reward_pool_fundings`\n15. `point_grants`\n16. `player_points`\n17. `dogpile_events`\n18. `crate_drops`\n19. `progress_events`\n20. `challenge_assignments`\n21. `bonus_completions`\n\nThe singleton `reward_pool` row is preserved and reset via UPDATE, not TRUNCATE."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8262916-ffcb-4b28-90e1-2b18f6c84ba5","uuid":"e9ef5db7-fd02-4689-9edc-1084fd758497","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:34:22.237Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` and report:\n1. How tests set up challenge_assignments and challenges\n2. How they verify assignment status changes\n3. The pattern for truncating tables in beforeEach\n4. The DB setup (createDb, migrations, etc.)\n5. The full list of tables in the TRUNCATE statement\n\nReport the key sections verbatim so I can understand the test patte